My Meme

As a life long football fan, I wanted to make a football based meme. My meme portrays the emotion I feel when the other team gets red carded verus when someone from the team I support (spurs) gets red carded. With the recent world cup. I decided to use pictures of Messi, who won the world cup with Argentina. Having that in mind, I decided to make a lighthearted meme using (magick).

library(magick)
#creating meme

messi_happy <- image_read("https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/oJoxvZug_vttJredFo0JjA--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU0MDtjZj13ZWJw/https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-12/069c36a0-8085-11ed-b7ff-ffcd557ae9cf") %>%
  image_scale(500)

messi_sad <- image_read("https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2021/08/720/405/Lionel-Messi-Leaving-FC-Barcelona.jpg?ve=1&tl=1")%>%
  image_scale(500)

apponent_redcard <- image_blank(width = 500,
                         height = 281,
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "When the other team gets red carded",
                 color = "#FFFF00",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
team_redcard <- image_blank(width = 500,
                         height = 281,
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "When your team gets red carded",
                 color = "#FFFF00",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

first_row <- c(apponent_redcard, messi_happy) %>%
  image_append()
second_row <- c(team_redcard, messi_sad) %>%
  image_append()
meme <- c(first_row, second_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
#saves a png image of my meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My Animation GIF

This GIF was inspired by my hobby of working out at the gym. I selected four different photos, the first three showing the emotion of being sad, whilst, the last one shows happiness, the complete opposite of the other three photos. The captions on each photo is a different types of exercise. The objective of this animation is to portray that I enjoy doing the bench press while not being the biggest fan of leg day, cardio and body weight training. This was done using a common GIF format.
